{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"Prior-art research (Zuul, LUCI CV/Chromium CQ, Gerrit plugins, Prow/Tide) resolved 6 of 7 design decisions by strong convergence (per reviewer approval to adopt convergent prior art):\n\n- **D1 liveness/status surface** → CQ pattern: bot posts per-change outcome BACK to the Gerrit change (comment + `Autosubmit` label state), which `land` reads via the Gerrit creds it already holds; PLUS a Zuul/Tide-style **read-only HTTP status endpoint** for bot liveness (heartbeat age) + queue-status (AC6). Resolves the \"file vs metric\" ambiguity: local heartbeat file backs the in-container HEALTHCHECK; the status endpoint surfaces it to remote `land`.\n- **D2 failed-rebase hand-back** → CQ \"reset\": on conflict / post-rebase `Verified -1` / N=5 exhaustion, the bot REMOVES `Autosubmit` + posts a comment naming the reason + writes S3's needs_rebase marker. Label-removal is the \"handed back\" signal remote `land` detects. This concretizes the previously-undefined S2 \"park\" mechanism.\n- **D3 time-to-land metric** → Zuul: emit a RAW queue-wait/resident_time timer; percentiles/buckets computed DOWNSTREAM (CloudWatch extended statistics), NOT hard-coded in the emitter. Dropped the fixed histogram buckets I had pinned.\n- **D5 Gerrit client** → reuse **pygerrit2** (thin wrapper) in the autolander tooling; do NOT reimplement and do NOT import `src/rebar`. Resolves the client-reuse BLOCK.\n- **D6 credential injection** → `land` uses the agent's ambient Gerrit HTTP credential (`.netrc` / git credential helper, via pygerrit2 HTTPBasicAuthFromNetrc); the bot uses RebarBotNava's SSM-backed HTTP password + `rebase_on_behalf_of_uploader` (keeps the human as uploader, forces CI re-verify).\n- **D7 emergency-stop + drain** → Zuul pause/graceful: a stop-consuming sentinel (state-volume file, checked each loop) → `paused`; graceful drain finishes the in-flight wipChain + writes its S3 outcome before exit.\n\nREMAINING (diverges — surfaced to reviewer): **D4** the plain-docker-compose unhealthy→restart mechanism (prior art is K8s liveness probes; not directly applicable)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783792966370212001,"uuid":"35feb063-00df-4c2a-92c2-b248477bad7d"}